BLACK HAT (Critical Judgment)
 * Risks: Templates can lead to "fill-in-the-blank" thinking where users provide shallow answers just to finish the form.
 * Weaknesses: A static template doesn't account for the varying importance of each hat depending on the specific problem.
 * Danger: Over-reliance on a single format might make the thinking process feel repetitive and stale over time.
YELLOW HAT (Optimism & Benefits)
 * Value: Templates ensure consistency across different projects and team members.
 * Benefits: They save significant time by removing the need to re-format every session.
 * Positives: Having a "Black Hat" section explicitly included makes it socially "safe" to be critical in a group setting without appearing negative.
